TY  - JOUR
T1  - Risk Preferences and the Macroeconomic Announcement Premium
AU  - Ai, Hengjie
AU  - Bansal, Ravi
Y1  - 2018/07/01
PY  - 2018
DA  - 2018/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA14607
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1383
EP  - 1430
VL  - 86
IS  - 4
KW  - Equity premium
KW  - announcement
KW  - Knightian uncertainty
KW  - robustness
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA14607
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper develops a revealed preference theory for the equity premium around macroeconomic announcements. Stock returns realized around pre-scheduled macroeconomic announcements, such as the employment report and the FOMC statements, account for 55% of the market equity premium. We provide a characterization theorem for the set of intertemporal preferences that generates a nonnegative announcement premium. Our theory establishes that the announcement premium identifies a significant deviation from time-separable expected utility and provides asset-market-based evidence for a large class of non-expected utility models. We also provide conditions under which asset prices may rise prior to some macroeconomic announcements and exhibit a pre-announcement drift.
ER  - 

